Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Dice @button mushrooms{8%oz}(diced into ¼-inch pieces). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Strip @rosemary{1/4%oz}(leaves stripped and finely chopped) leaves from stems until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped).

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water (1¼ cups for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Add garlic, chopped rosemary, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While mushrooms cook, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz can}, @flour{1%tbsp}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, half the @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1 cup plain water, and @sugar{3/4%tsp}. (For 4 servings, use all the vinegar, 2 cups water, and 1 1/2 tsp sugar.)

To pan with mushrooms, add a drizzle of oil and @tomato paste{1.5%oz}; cook, stirring, until tomato paste darkens, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add tomato-flour mixture to pan; season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir drained rigatoni into pan with sauce, adding splashes of reserved pasta cooking water until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between bowls; top each bowl with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Garnish with parsley and serve.

> Here's the weeknight vegan dinner idea you've been coveting! Earthy, meaty button mushrooms make the perfect stand-in for ground meat.

> You'll be craving this veg version from now on.